This paper deals with the design of routing algorithms for route-restricted overlay networks, which are a type of network commonly used in payment and social networks. The paper specifically focuses on the problem of Byzantine fault tolerance in distributed spanning tree algorithms. Given this focus, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), which deals with the design and analysis of network protocols and architectures. Other likely categories include cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which are all relevant to the paper's focus on distributed algorithms, security, and social networks.
